{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:19:39,880", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_execution_result", "line": 199, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:19:39.880607\", \"task_id\": \"task4\", \"agent_id\": \"4\", \"objective\": \"Develop the Pygame-based GUI and main game loop: render the grid, animations, current score, next tetromino preview, and integrate controls with mechanics modules.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom enum import Enum\\nfrom collections import namedtuple\\n\\n# Initialize Pygame\\npygame.init()\\n\\n# Constants (can be adjusted)\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\nCELL_SIZE = 30\\nSCREEN_WIDTH = 600  # Increased for score and next piece display\\nSCREEN_HEIGHT = GRID_HEIGHT * CELL_SIZE\\nFPS = 30\\n\\n# Colors\\nBLACK = (0, 0, 0)\\nWHITE = (255, 255, 255)\\nGRAY = (128, 128, 128)\\n\\n# Data Structures\\nPoint = namedtuple('Point', ['x', 'y'])\\nPieceType = Enum('PieceType', ['I', 'O', 'T', 'S', 'Z', 'J', 'L'])\\nGameStateEnum = Enum('GameState', ['PLAYING', 'GAME_OVER'])\\n\\nTETROMINO_SHAPES = {\\n    PieceType.I: [\\n        [Point(0,1), Point(1,1), Point(2,1), Point(3,1)],\\n        [Point(2,0), Point(2,1), Point(2,2), Point(2,3)],\\n        [Point(0,2), Point(1,2), Point(2,2), Point(3,2)],\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(1,1), Point(1,2), Point(1,3)],\\n    ],\\n    PieceType.O: [\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(2,0), Point(1,1), Point(2,1)],\\n    ] * 4,\\n    PieceType.T: [\\n        [Point(1,0), Point(0,...\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"duration_seconds\": 0.0}"}
